rComments: The worst super vised in my academic life! He never can supervise a grad student. Don't waste your time and don't pick him as your PhD supervisor. Check his resume before taking him. He never could finish a grad student as a normal prof. Most of his graduated students was from other profs and he was a co-superviser.
He looks funny and he tries to show that he is very kind, but he is not helpful at all.
Avoid him! He is very dangerous.

He's very kind and always ready to help his students. There are a few assignments which is good and they help bring up your average. The material was not super difficult but you have to study in order to succeed. Loved him and would recommend him to everyone.

Great prof, super sweet and there for his students. Sometimes the material can be a bit confusing but he is more than happy to help you out. Responds to e-mails very quickly even on weekends. Recommend him!

Avoid at all costs. Only good thing is that he bumps up your grade by 30 points for the midterms and exam because more than half of the class fails miserably. Do not take this class for "fun" or as a science elective, there are much better ones out there. If you are really interested in the subject matter, try your best to take it in English
